2.20	Villa_Durazzo-Pallavicini	Villa Durazzo-Pallavicini	The Villa Durazzo-Pallavicini is a villa with notable 19th century park in the English romantic style and a small botanical garden. The villa now houses the Museo di Archeologia Ligure, and is located at Via Pallavicini, 13, immediately next to the railway station in Pegli, a suburb of Genoa, Italy. The park and botanical garden are open daily.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Villa_Durazzo-Pallavicini_-_the_lake.JPG/300px-Villa_Durazzo-Pallavicini_-_the_lake.JPG
